'''''Porgy and Bess''''' is a 1958 album by [[jazz]] musician [[Miles Davis]] which he and [[Gil Evans]] arranged from [[George Gershwin]]'s [[opera]] ''[[Porgy and Bess]]''. 
The album was recorded in four sessions on [[July 22]], [[July 29]], [[August 4]] and [[August 18]], [[1958]]. It is the second collaboration between Davis and Evans, the first being ''[[Miles Ahead]]'', and has garnered much critical acclaim since its release, being acknowledged by music critics as the best of their collaborations.<ref>[http://72.14.205.104/search?q=cache:f6GHBikMJsAJ:cd.ciao.co.uk/Porgy_And_Bess_Remastered_Miles_Davis__5969765+JazzTimes+(8/97,+p.106)+-+%22...PORGY+AND+BESS&hl=en&ct=clnk&cd=2&gl=us Album/Product notes and reviews]</ref> For many jazz critics, this recording is regarded as historic.<ref>[http://www.allaboutjazz.com/php/news.php?id=17228 Porgy and Bess Presentation ''Zankel Hall'', NYC]</ref> 

